5.
    a.
        An automated system is a system which can run without human intervention
    b.
        The microprocessor takes in data input from the sensors and manipulates it in order to send out corrective commands to the plough to maintain a straight line without human intervention.
    c.
        1.
            The farmer does not have to babysit the plough
        2.
            Many such ploughs can run, or ploughs can run continuously, allowing for more fields to be prepared for seed-planting in the same time.
    d.
        The plough may gather data during its ploughing such as which areas of the field require more ploughing, what sort of tools to plough which part of the field, the most optimal route through the field, the most efficient way to remain upright, what sort of actions to take when in danger of falling over, and when ploughing should happen to be most efficient.
6.
    a.
        Cookies are small text files stored by a web browser. Session cookies are temporary text files that are deleted when the web browser is closed. Persistent cookies are permanent text files that are stored on a user's secondary storage device until they are manually deleted or they expire.
    b?
        1.
            Keeping track of a user's behavior, e.g. in order to serve them targeted advertisements
        2.
            Allowing a user to automatically log in to websites between browsing sessions
        3.
            Keeping track of session variables like authentication codes to remove the need of multiple authorisation attempts per session
7.
    The purpose of the IDE is to allow the programmer to program more efficiently. IDEs offer features such as:
        - An integrated translator to run and test programs
        - An error-diagnostic to report errors when those programs are ran
        - Auto-correct, to automatically correct minor typing mistakes or misinputs
        - Auto-complete, to offer suggestions or options as to automatically completing variable names
        - Pretty-print, to highlight key commands to make the code easier to read
    These features allow the programmer to develop with more confidence and faster, and aid the programmer in that manner.
